 in the [[2002 FIBA World Championship]] and the [[2004 Summer Olympic Games]].<ref>[http://www.insidehoops.com/usa-2006-08-030506.shtml Team USA 2006\u201308 Announced]. Insidehoops.com (March 5, 2006). Retrieved on 2012-05-27.</ref> After missing out in the [[2006 FIBA World Championship]] due to personal reasons, on August 20, 2007, Billups was selected to be a part of Team USA that competed at the [[FIBA Americas Championship 2007|2007 FIBA Americas Championship]], a qualifying tournament for the [[2008 Summer Olympics|Beijing Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.usabasketball.com/news_archive.php?news_page=07_msnt_teamnamed&page=msnt |title=USA Men's Team Announced For FIBA Americas Championship |accessdate=August 24, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090113134918/http://www.usabasketball.com/news_archive.php?news_page=07_msnt_teamnamed&page=msnt |archivedate=January 13, 2009 }}. usabasketball.com. August 20, 2007</ref> Coming off the bench, he along with the other new members of the team including [[List of NBA All-Stars|All Star]] [[Kobe Bryant]] helped USA go unbeaten at the tournament held in [[Las Vegas]] and earn a spot at next Summer Olympics. On June 17, 2008, Billups announced he would not compete for a spot to be on the Olympic squad stating family reasons though he did say \"they'll be fine. And when they win the gold, I'll feel like I had a big hand in regaining our dominance because of what we did last summer.\"<ref>[http://sports.espn.go.com/oly/olybb/news/story?id=3449236 Citing family reasons, Billups pulls out of consideration for Beijing]. Sports.espn.go.com (June 17, 2008). Retrieved on 2012-05-27.</ref> During the tournament, Team USA went unbeaten on their way to their first gold medal since the [[2000 Olympics]], defeating Spain in the final.<ref>Brian Mahoney [https://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/2008-08-24-1497081242_x.htm US hoops back on top, beats Spain for gold medal]. ''USA Today'' (August 24, 2008)</ref>\n\n==Television career==\nBillups joined [[ESPN]] in the 2014-15 NBA season as a studio analyst on ''[[SportsCenter]]'' and other programming.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://espnpressroom.com/us/bios/chauncey-billups/|title=Chauncey Billups|website=ESPN Press Room U.S.|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref> The following season, Billups joined ''[[NBA Countdown]]'' as a studio analyst on Wednesdays. In the ensuing three seasons, he began splitting time between the studio and working as a game analyst on selected telecasts.  Finally, on August 16, 2019, Billups announced that he was exiting his role on ''NBA Countdown'' to become the game analyst on [[Los Angeles Clippers]] telecasts as part of that team's restructuring of the broadcast crew due to the retirement of longtime play-by-play announcer [[Ralph Lawler]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/sports/story/2019-08-16/chauncey-billups-clippers-broadcast-analyst|title=Chauncey Billups joining Clippers broadcasts as television analyst|date=2019-08-16|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref> Billups indicated that he would also continue to call selected NBA game telecasts on ESPN in addition to his duties with the Clippers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://awfulannouncing.com/nba/chauncey-billups-nba-countdown-clippers-espn.html|title=Chauncey Billups will leave NBA Countdown for game analyst work|date=2019-08-17|website=Awful Announcing|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBillups is married to his wife, Piper, and they have three daughters, Cydney,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.texassports.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=7430|title=Cydney Billups - 2017 Soccer Roster - University of Texas Athletics|website=www.texassports.com}}</ref> Ciara, and Cenaiya.<ref>[http://www.rotoworld.com/content/playerpages/playerbreakingnews.asp?sport=NBA&id=468&line=68045&spln=1 Fantasy Basketball Breaking News \u2013] {{Webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/655aC1dqT?url=http://www.rotoworld.com/content/playerpages/playerbreakingnews.asp?sport=NBA&id=468&line=68045&spln=1 |date=January 30, 2012 }}. Rotoworld.com. Retrieved on May 27, 2012.</ref> His friend, NBA player [[Kevin Garnett]], is the godfather to Ciara. His younger brother, [[Rodney Billups|Rodney]], played point guard for the [[Denver Pioneers|University of Denver]] from 2002-2005, was drafted in the [[NBA Development League]], played professionally in Europe, and went on to a coaching career, becoming head coach of the Denver Pioneers in 2016.<ref>[http://denverpioneers.cstv.com/sports/m-baskbl/mtt/billups_rodney00.html CSTV.com: #1 in College Sports]. Denverpioneers.cstv.com. Retrieved on May 27, 2012.</ref><ref>[http://www.nba.com/dleague/news/draft_2006.html NBA Development League Announces 2006 Draft Results] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070219055015/http://www.nba.com/dleague/news/draft_2006.html |date=February 19, 2007 }}. nba.com. November 2, 2006</ref> Billups is the [[first cousin]] of [[running back]] [[LenDale White]].<ref name=\"fivethings\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nba.com/playoffs2006/fivethings_billups_060404.html |title=Five Things You Didn't Know About Chauncey Billups |date=June 2006 |accessdate=February 21, 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070415135729/http://www.nba.com/playoffs2006/fivethings_billups_060404.html |archivedate=April 15, 2007 }}</ref>\n\nBillups wore the #4 through high school and college and at times during his professional career because he idolized former Pistons guard [[Joe Dumars]], the Pistons President of Basketball Operations during his time at Detroit.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nba.com/pistons/features/fsndetroit_spotlight_cb.html |title=PISTONS: FSN SPOTLIGHT \u2013 Chauncey Billups |accessdate=February 20, 2007 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090115065042/http://www.nba.com/pistons/features/fsndetroit_spotlight_cb.html |archivedate=January 15, 2009 }}. nba.com.</ref> His favorite [[National Football League|NFL]] team is the [[Denver Broncos]].<ref name=\"fivethings\" />\n\nBillups was featured on the cover of the video game ''[[NBA Ballers: Phenom]]'' and is the player's mentor.\n\nOn June 16, 2008, Billups appeared at [[Joe Louis Arena]] for a [[Barack Obama]] rally.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wxyz.com/content/news/2008vote/story.aspx?content_id=6c1e0ad6-e892-4f43-ad65-454ca4a36e0e |title=Billups Makes Surprise Appearance for Obama |accessdate=August 7, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080623020136/http://www.wxyz.com/content/news/2008vote/story.aspx?content_id=6c1e0ad6-e892-4f43-ad65-454ca4a36e0e |archivedate=June 23, 2008 }} (June 17, 2008)</ref>\n\n=== Sexual assault allegation ===\nIn 1997, Billups and fellow former Celtic [[Ron Mercer]] were accused of sexually assaulting a woman at the home of teammate [[Antoine Walker]]. According to a civil suit, Billups, Mercer, and Walker's roommate, Michael Irvin, assaulted the woman at Walker's condo after leaving a Boston comedy club on November 9, 1997. A medical examination on the following day revealed injuries consistent with the victim's testimony.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://secure.pqarchiver.com/boston/doc/405323103.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Oct+6%2C+1999&author=Murphy%2C+Shelley&pub=Boston+Globe&edition=&startpage=B.2&desc=Renewed+suit%3A+Walker+failed+to+stop+rape|title=Renewed suit: Walker failed to stop rape|last=Murphy|first=Shelley|date=October 6, 1999|work=The Boston Globe|access-date=January 22, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180123131509/https://secure.pqarchiver.com/boston/doc/405323103.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Oct+6%2C+1999&author=Murphy%2C+Shelley&pub=Boston+Globe&edition=&startpage=B.2&desc=Renewed+suit%3A+Walker+failed+to+stop+rape|archive-date=January 23, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> No criminal charges were filed, but Billups and Mercer settled a civil suit in 2000.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/sports/2000/01/13/two-former-celtics-settle-lawsuit-in-rape-case/9c07ef60-f73f-4a65-a7d7-1c99ef0ba384/|title=Two Former Celtics Settle Lawsuit in Rape Case|date=January 13, 2000|work=Washington Post|access-date=January 23, 2018|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Sports}}\n*[[List of National Basketball Association career games played leaders]]\n*[[List of National Basketball Association career assists leaders]]\n*[[List of National Basketball Association career 3-point scoring leaders]]\n*[[List of National Basketball Association career free throw scoring leaders]]\n*[[List of National Basketball Association career playoff assists leaders]]\n*[[List of National Basketball Association career playoff 3-point scoring leaders]]\n*[[List of National Basketball Association career playoff free throw scoring leaders]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|35em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Chauncey Billups}}\n*{{basketballstats|nba=chauncey_billups|bbr=b/billuch01}}\n*[http://www.jockbio.com/Bios/Billups/Billups_bio.html JockBio.com Biography]\n\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{Detroit Pistons 2003\u201304 NBA champions}}\n{{NBA Finals MVPs}}\n{{J. Walter Kennedy Citizenship Award}}\n{{NBA Sportsmanship Award Winners}}\n{{Twyman\u2013Stokes Teammate Award}}\n{{United States squad 2007 FIBA Americas Championship}}\n{{United States Men Basketball Squad 2010 FIBA World Championship}}\n{{1997 NCAA Men's Basketball Consensus All-Americans}}\n{{1997 NBA Draft}}\n{{Detroit Pistons}}\n{{NBA on ABC}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Billups, Chauncey}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:African-American basketball players]]\n[[Category:All-American college men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:American expatriate basketball people in Canada]]\n[[Category:American men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Basketball players from Colorado]]\n[[Category:Big3 players]]\n[[Category:Boston Celtics draft picks]]\n[[Category:Boston Celtics players]]\n[[Category:Colorado Buffaloes men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Denver Nuggets players]]\n[[Category:Detroit Pistons players]]\n[[Category:FIBA World Championship-winning players]]\n[[Category:Los Angeles Clippers players]]\n[[Category:McDonald's High School All-Americans]]\n[[Category:Minnesota Timberwolves players]]\n[[Category:National Basketball Association All-Stars]]\n[[Category:National Basketball Association players with retired numbers]]\n[[Category:New York Knicks players]]\n[[Category:Parade High School All-Americans (boys' basketball)]]\n[[Category:Point guards]]\n[[Category:Shooting guards]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Denver]]\n[[Category:Toronto Raptors players]]\n[[Category:United States men's national basketball team players]]\n[[Category:2010 FIBA World Championship players]]\n", "name_user": "188.192.225.22", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(adjusted image position slightly)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chauncey_Billups"}
{"title_page": "Ketmen Ridge", "text_new": "{{short description|Mountain range in the Tian Shan system}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{copy edit|date=March 2020}}{{more footnotes|date=March 2020}}}}\n\n{{Infobox mountain\n| name              = '''Ketmen Ridge'''\n| other_name        = \n| etymology         = \n| native_name       = \n| native_name_lang  = \n| translation       = \n| pronunciation     = \n| photo             = \n| photo_size        = \n| photo_alt         = \n| photo_caption     = \n| map               = \n| map_image         = \n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n| map_relief        = \n| map_size          = \n| location          = Uygur and Rayimbek districts, Almaty region, Republic of Kazakhstan\n| label             = \n| label_position    = \n| elevation         = \n| elevation_m       = \n| elevation_ft      = \n| elevation_ref     = \n| prominence        = \n| prominence_m      = \n| prominence_ft     = \n| prominence_ref    = \n| isolation         = \n| isolation_km      = \n| isolation_mi      = \n| isolation_ref     = \n| parent_peak       = \n| listing           = \n| range             = \n| coordinates       = \n| coordinates_ref   = \n| topo              = \n| type              = \n| age               = \n| geology           = \n| volcanic_arc      = \n| volcanic_belt     = \n| volcanic_field    = \n| volcanic_arc/belt = \n| last_eruption     = \n| first_ascent      = \n| easiest_route     = \n| normal_route      = \n| access            = \n| child             = \n| embedded          = \n}}\n\nThe '''Ketmen Ridge''' is located south of the [[Trans-Ili Alatau|Zailiyskiy Alatau]] in northern [[Tian Shan]]. The ridge is on the territory of the [[Uyghurs|Uyghur]] and [[Raiymbek District|Raiymbek]] districts of the [[Almaty Region|Almaty region]] which falls within the [[Republic of Kazakhstan]] and [[China]]. The total length of the ridge is 310 km, 160 km of which lies in Kazakhstan. The width of the ridge is about 40\u201350 km. The highest point of the range is Mount Aspan at 3,652 m. The ridge is adjacent to the K\u00fcng\u00f6y Ala-Too Range in the west and the Narat Ridge in the east. The northern slopes of the ridge pass into the Ili Valley. Ketmen Ridge forms the southern border of Semirechye. \n\nThe ridge is composed of igneous and sedimentary rocks, such as effusions, [[granite]], and [[limestone]]. The slopes are steep with gentle peaks below the snow line. The ridge has a [[permafrost]] zone but does not have glaciation or snowfields. It contains [[steppe]] and [[taiga]] forests, which consist mainly of spruce trees and meadows in high-altitude zones. At the foot of the southern slope of the ridge, steppe bison remains have been found.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\nThe eponymous Ketmen pass is located at an altitude of 3,040 meters above sea level in the Eastern part of the mountain range. A caravan trail from the Ili valley to the Kegen-Tekes hollow runs through the pass, which connects the northern slope in the Ketmen gorge and southern slope of the ridge of the Shalkudysu river valley.\n\n==Flora and Fauna==\nThe Ketmen ridge has mountainous flora; Research found the Ketmen ridge home to 1890 species of vascular plants, which are angiosperms, dicots, and monocots. <ref>Sadyrova GA. Flora of the Ketpen-Temerlik ridge. (2009) in Rakhimova YV, et al. </ref>\n\nEighty-four species from 11 genera of rust fungi were found. The most abundant genera found were 48 species of Puccinia and 12 species of Uromyces <ref>Rakhimova YV, Yermekova BD, Kyzmetova LA. \"Checklist of rust fungi from Ketmen ridge.\" Plant Pathology & Quarantine 7(2): 110\u2013135 (2017).</ref>.\n\n== Source and links ==\n\n* https://www.tripadvisor.com.my/Attraction_Review-g2350619-d15873720-Reviews-Ketmen_Ridge-Almaty_Region.html\n* \u041a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u0445\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d. \u041e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0433\u0435\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 / \u0422. \u041f. \u0424\u0438\u043b\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430 (\u0440\u0435\u0434.). \u2014 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u044f. \u2014 \u041e\u043c\u0441\u043a: \u041e\u043c\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0444\u0430\u0431\u0440\u0438\u043a\u0430, 2011. \u2014 {{ISBN|978-5-9523-0332-4}}\n* \u041a\u0435\u0442\u043f\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0445\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0435\u0442 // \u041a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u0445\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d. \u041d\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u044d\u043d\u0446\u0438\u043a\u043b\u043e\u043f\u0435\u0434\u0438\u044f. \u2014 \u0410\u043b\u043c\u0430\u0442\u044b: \u049a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u049b \u044d\u043d\u0446\u0438\u043a\u043b\u043e\u043f\u0435\u0434\u0438\u044f\u0441\u044b, 2005. \u2014 \u0422. III. \u2014 {{ISBN|9965-9746-4-0}}.\n* \u041a\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0441\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0418\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0442\u0430 \u0430\u0440\u0445\u0435\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0438 / \u0413\u043b. \u0440\u0435\u0434. \u041d. \u0410. \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432. \u2014 \u041c. : \u042f\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0430\u0432\u044f\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u044b, 2012. \u2014 \u0412\u044b\u043f. 227. \u2014 \u0421. 191, 193. \u2014 {{ISBN|978-5-9551-0634-2}}.\n*Rakhimova YV, Yermekova BD, Kyzmetova LA. (2017). Checklist of rust fungi from Ketmen ridge (southeast of Kazakhstan). Retrieved March 30, 2020 from http://www.plantpathologyquarantine.org/pdf/PPQ_7_2_4.pdf\n\n{{coord|43|18|N|79|22|E|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Mountains of Kazakhstan]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Mountain range in the Tian Shan system}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{copy edit|date=March 2020}}{{more footnotes|date=March 2020}}}}\n\n{{Infobox mountain\n| name              = '''Ketmen Ridge'''\n| other_name        = \n| etymology         = \n| native_name       = \n| native_name_lang  = \n| translation       = \n| pronunciation     = \n| photo             = \n| photo_size        = \n| photo_alt         = \n| photo_caption     = \n| map               = \n| map_image         = \n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n| map_relief        = \n| map_size          = \n| location          = Uygur and Rayimbek districts, Almaty region, Republic of Kazakhstan\n| label             = \n| label_position    = \n| elevation         = \n| elevation_m       = \n| elevation_ft      = \n| elevation_ref     = \n| prominence        = \n| prominence_m      = \n| prominence_ft     = \n| prominence_ref    = \n| isolation         = \n| isolation_km      = \n| isolation_mi      = \n| isolation_ref     = \n| parent_peak       = \n| listing           = \n| range             = \n| coordinates       = \n| coordinates_ref   = \n| topo              = \n| type              = \n| age               = \n| geology           = \n| volcanic_arc      = \n| volcanic_belt     = \n| volcanic_field    = \n| volcanic_arc/belt = \n| last_eruption     = \n| first_ascent      = \n| easiest_route     = \n| normal_route      = \n| access            = \n| child             = \n| embedded          = \n}}\n\nThe '''Ketmen Ridge''' is located south of the [[Trans-Ili Alatau|Zailiyskiy Alatau]] in Northern [[Tian Shan]]. The Ridge is on the territory of the [[Uyghurs|Uyghur]] and [[Raiymbek District|Raiymbek]] districts of the [[Almaty Region|Almaty region]] which falls within the [[Republic of Kazakhstan]] and [[China]]. The total length of the Ridge is 310 km, 160 km of which lies in Kazakhstan. The width of the Ridge is about 40\u201350 km. The highest point of the range is Mount Aspan at 3,652 m.\nThe Ridge is adjacent to the K\u00fcng\u00f6y Ala-Too Range in the West and the Narat Ridge in the East. The Northern slopes of the Ridge pass into the Ili Valley. Ketmen Ridge forms the southern border of Semirechye. \n\nThe Ridge is composed of igneous and sedimentary rocks, such as effusions, [[granite]], and [[limestone]]. The slopes are steep with gentle peaks below the snow line. The Ridge has a [[permafrost]] zone but does not have glaciation or snowfields. It contains [[steppe]] and [[taiga]] forests, which consist mainly of spruce trees and meadows in high-altitude zones. At the foot of the southern slope of the ridge, steppe bison remains have been found {{citation needed|date=April 2020}}.\n\nThe eponymous Ketmen pass is located at an altitude of 3,040 meters above sea level in the Eastern part of the mountain range. A caravan trail from the Ili valley to the Kegen-Tekes hollow runs through the pass, which connects the Northern slope in the Ketmen gorge and southern slope of the Ridge of the Shalkudysu river valley.\n\n==Flora and Fauna==\nThe Ketmen ridge has mountainous flora; Research found the Ketmen ridge home to 1890 species of vascular plants, which are angiosperms, dicots, and monocots. <ref>Sadyrova GA. Flora of the Ketpen-Temerlik ridge. (2009) in Rakhimova YV, et al. </ref>\n\nEighty-four species from 11 genera of rust fungi were found. The most abundant genera found were 48 species of Puccinia and 12 species of Uromyces <ref>Rakhimova YV, Yermekova BD, Kyzmetova LA. \"Checklist of rust fungi from Ketmen ridge.\" Plant Pathology & Quarantine 7(2): 110\u2013135 (2017).</ref>.\n\n== Source and links ==\n\n* https://www.tripadvisor.com.my/Attraction_Review-g2350619-d15873720-Reviews-Ketmen_Ridge-Almaty_Region.html\n* \u041a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u0445\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d. \u041e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0433\u0435\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 / \u0422. \u041f. \u0424\u0438\u043b\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430 (\u0440\u0435\u0434.). \u2014 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u