{"title_page": "Bad Boys for Life", "text_new": "{{distinguish|Bad Boy for Life}}\n{{short description|2020 film directed by Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah}}\n{{Use American English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Bad Boys for Life\n| image          = Bad Boys for Life poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah|{{unbulleted list|Adil El Arbi|Bilall Fallah}}]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Jerry Bruckheimer]]\n* [[Will Smith]]\n* [[Doug Belgrad]]\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{plainlist|\n* Chris Bremner\n* [[Peter Craig]]\n* [[Joe Carnahan]]\n}}\n| story          = {{plainlist|\n* Peter Craig\n* Joe Carnahan\n}}\n| based on       = {{Based on|Characters|[[George Gallo]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* Will Smith\n* [[Martin Lawrence]]\n* [[Vanessa Hudgens]]\n* [[Alexander Ludwig]] \n* [[Charles Melton (actor)|Charles Melton]]\n* [[Paola N\u00fa\u00f1ez]]\n* [[Kate del Castillo]]\n* [[Nicky Jam]]\n* [[Joe Pantoliano]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Lorne Balfe]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Lorne Balfe to Score 'Bad Boys for Life' |url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2019/07/23/lorne-balfe-to-score-bad-boys-for-life/ |website=Film Music Reporter |accessdate=July 23, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723215204/http://filmmusicreporter.com/2019/07/23/lorne-balfe-to-score-bad-boys-for-life/ |archive-date=July 23, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n| cinematography = Robrecht Heyvaert\n| editing        = {{plainlist |\n* Dan Lebental\n* [[Peter McNulty (film editor)|Peter McNulty]]\n}}\n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Columbia Pictures]]<ref name=\"THRreview\"/>\n* 2.0 Entertainment<ref name=\"THRreview\"/>\n*[[Don Simpson]]/[[Jerry Bruckheimer Films]]<ref name=\"THRreview\"/>\n* [[Overbrook Entertainment]]<ref name=\"THRreview\"/><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/sony-overbrook-entertainment-12-oclock-boys-film-1202463691/ |title=Sony & Overbrook Entertainment Team On Film About Dirt-Bike Riders |access-date=May 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190509124227/https://deadline.com/2018/09/sony-overbrook-entertainment-12-oclock-boys-film-1202463691/ |archive-date=May 9, 2019 |url-status=live |work=deadline.com}}</ref>\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Sony Pictures Releasing]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|01|17}}\n| runtime        = 124 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/bad-boys-life-film-0|title=Bad Boys for Life (15)|website=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|date=January 14, 2020|accessdate=January 15, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115155724/https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/bad-boys-life-film-0|archive-date=January 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| country        = Belgium<br>United States<ref>{{cite web |title= Bad Boys for Life (2020) |url= https://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/5ddbd53927c08 |website= [[British Film Institute]] |access-date= January 18, 2020 }}</ref><ref name=\"NUM\"/>\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $90 million<ref name=BOM/>\n| gross          = $419.1 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{Cite web |url= https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl1182631425/?ref_=bo_da_table_1 |title=Bad Boys for Life (2020) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]] |accessdate=April 12, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"NUM\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Bad-Boys-For-Life-(Bad-Boys-3)-(2020)#tab=summary|title=Bad Boys for Life (2020)|website=[[The Numbers (website)|The Numbers]]|accessdate=March 17, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230202109/https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Bad-Boys-For-Life-(Bad-Boys-3)-(2020)#tab=summary|archive-date=December 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Bad Boys for Life''''' is a 2020 American [[action comedy]] film directed by [[Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah]] and written by Chris Bremner, [[Peter Craig]] and [[Joe Carnahan]]. The sequel to ''[[Bad Boys II]]'' (2003), it is the third installment in the [[Bad Boys (franchise)|''Bad Boys'' franchise]] and is based on a story by Craig and Carnahan. The film stars [[Will Smith]], [[Martin Lawrence]], [[Vanessa Hudgens]], [[Alexander Ludwig]], [[Charles Melton (actor)|Charles Melton]], [[Paola N\u00fa\u00f1ez]], [[Kate del Castillo]], [[Nicky Jam]], and [[Joe Pantoliano]]. Smith co-produced the film with [[Jerry Bruckheimer]] and [[Doug Belgrad]]. In ''Bad Boys for Life'', [[Miami]] detectives Mike Lowrey and Marcus Burnett investigate a string of murders tied to Lowrey's troubled past.\n\nA third ''Bad Boys'' film was discussed after the success of the second, with [[Michael Bay]] stating he would be interested in returning to direct, but budgetary constraints made going ahead difficult. The film went through several attempts to enter production over the course of a decade, with a variety of writers and directors attached. The project was eventually finalized and green-lit in October 2018, and filming began the following year, lasting from January to June 2019. [[Principal photography]] took place in [[Atlanta]], [[Miami]] and [[Mexico City]].\n\n''Bad Boys for Life'' was theatrically released in the United States on January 17, 2020, by [[Sony Pictures Releasing]], through [[Columbia Pictures]]. The film received mostly positive reviews from critics,<ref name=\"obenson\" /> and has grossed $419 million worldwide, currently making it the [[2020 in film|highest-grossing film of 2020]]. It is also the highest-grossing installment of the series and the biggest January release of all time.\n\n==Plot==\nIsabel Aretas, widow of cartel kingpin Benito, escapes from a Mexican prison with the aid of her son Armando. Isabel sends Armando to Miami, tasking him with recovering a substantial stash of money his father Benito had hidden, as well as assassinating the people responsible for his father's arrest and eventual death in prison. Isabel demands that Armando kill Miami detective Mike Lowrey last.\n\nIn Miami, Mike accompanies his partner Marcus Burnett to the birth of his first grandson. Desiring to spend more time with his family, the aging Marcus tells Mike he intends to retire, to Mike's chagrin. During a party celebrating Marcus' grandson, Mike is shot by Armando and left in a coma for months. Chastised by Isabel for targeting Mike first, Armando continues to assassinate other targets on his list during Mike's convalescence.\n\nFollowing Mike's recovery, he is determined to seek revenge and unsuccessfully attempts to recruit the now-retired Marcus, causing a fall out between them. Mike violently obtains the identity of arms dealer Booker Grassie from an informant. Realizing that Mike will not heed orders to stay away from the investigation, Captain Howard reluctantly allows him to work with the tech-driven team in charge, the Advanced Miami Metro Operations (AMMO), led by Mike's ex-girlfriend Rita. While the team surveils Grassie at an arms deal, Mike determines that the buyers intend to kill Grassie and intervenes, but fails to save him. Later, Marcus is called by Carver Remy, an old informant who believes the assassin is after him. Marcus contacts Mike and the pair travel to Carver, but are too late to save him. Armando escapes after a fistfight with Mike.\n\nCaptain Howard later reveals his intentions to retire as well, offering advice to Mike that he needs to find a path forward in life. He is abruptly assassinated by Armando moments later. The captain's death pulls Marcus out of retirement, but he intends to work as a team with AMMO. They track down Grassie's accountant, who leads them to Lorenzo \"Zway-Lo\" Rodriguez. They infiltrate Zway-Lo's birthday party leading to a destructive car chase. Armando arrives in a helicopter to rescue Zway-Lo but kills him when he blocks Armando's ability to shoot the pursuing Mike. As he lines up a shot, Armando tells Mike \"Hasta el fuego\". Gunfire from Marcus creates cover for Mike, who falls into the river below.\n\nAMMO is shut down because of the failed operation. In private, Mike reveals to Marcus that Armando may be his son. Before partnering with Marcus, Mike worked as an undercover officer in the Aretas cartel where he met Isabel. They fell in love and intended to run away together, using \"Hasta el fuego\" as a secret catchphrase. Mike ultimately remained loyal to the police, realizing how dangerous Isabel had become. Despite Mike's opposition, Marcus and AMMO join him in Mexico City to confront her.\n\nAt the Hidalgo Palace, Mike meets Isabel and scolds her for concealing the truth from him. A shootout quickly ensues between AMMO and Isabel's men. Marcus shoots the pilot of Isabel's support helicopter, causing it to crash into the central lobby and starting a fire. Marcus confronts Isabel, while Mike tries to explain the truth to Armando. Armando begins to beat up Mike, but he refuses to retaliate. Demanding the truth from his mother, Isabel confirms to Armando that Mike is his father. Unable to kill his father, Armando steps back, and Isabel, while aiming for Mike, inadvertently shoots Armando in the chest. Enraged, she attempts to finish Mike, but Rita intervenes and shoots Isabel several times, sending Isabel falling into the flames below. Marcus then begins to fall into the flames, but is saved by both Mike and Armando. Carrying Armando outside, Mike tells his son that things will not be so good for him due to the crimes he committed, but that he would always be there for him.\n\nReturning to Miami, Rita has been promoted to police captain, and the team celebrates her promotion. Mike arranges for Marcus and Theresa to go on a retreat while he takes care of their grandchild. Sometime later, Mike visits a remorseful Armando in prison, and Armando tells Mike that he is atoning for his sins. Mike then enlists his help for a mission, informing him that it would be a chance to pay back some of his debt, and Armando accepts.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Will Smith]] as Detective Lieutenant Michael Eugene \"Mike\" Lowrey\n* [[Martin Lawrence]] as Detective Lieutenant Marcus Miles Burnett\n* [[Vanessa Hudgens]] as Kelly<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/film/bad-boys-life-trailer-reveals-20816984|title=Bad Boys for Life trailer reveals action-packed scenes for Will Smith sequel|last=Knight|first=Lewis|date=2019-11-05|website=mirror|access-date=2019-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191113171551/https://www.mirror.co.uk/film/bad-boys-life-trailer-reveals-20816984|archive-date=November 13, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Alexander Ludwig]] as Dorn\n* [[Charles Melton (actor)|Charles Melton]] as Rafe\n* [[Paola N\u00fa\u00f1ez]] as Rita Secada, head of AMMO, Mike's ex-girlfriend\n* [[Jacob Scipio]] as Armando Aretas\n* [[Kate del Castillo]] as Isabel Aretas\n* [[Nicky Jam]] as Lorenzo \"Zway-Lo\" Rodr\u00edguez<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/bad-boys-sequel-nicky-jam-1203111208/ |title=Reggaeton Star Nicky Jam Joins 'Bad Boys' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |last=Kroll |first=Justin |last2=Kroll |first2=Justin |date=January 18, 2019 |website=Variety |language=en|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190119174400/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/bad-boys-sequel-nicky-jam-1203111208/|archive-date=January 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Joe Pantoliano]] as Captain Conrad Howard\n* [[Theresa Randle]] as Theresa Burnett, Marcus' wife.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/1054885-theresa-randle-will-return-as-marcus-wife-in-bad-boys-for-life |title=Theresa Randle Will Return as Marcus' Wife in Bad Boys for Life |first=Max |last=Evry|website=[[Comingsoon.net]]|date=March 30, 2019|access-date=April 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190405115510/https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/1054885-theresa-randle-will-return-as-marcus-wife-in-bad-boys-for-life |archive-date=April 5, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Massi Furlan]] as Lee Taglin\n* Dennis Greene as Reggie  \n* Bianca Bethune as Megan Burnett, Marcus' daughter\n* [[Michael Bay]] as Wedding MC\n* [[DJ Khaled]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/dj-khaled-bad-boys-sequel-1203108932/ |title=DJ Khaled Joins 'Bad Boys' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |last=Kroll |first=Justin |last2=Kroll |first2=Justin |date=January 15, 2019 |website=Variety |language=en|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190116095949/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/dj-khaled-bad-boys-sequel-1203108932/|archive-date=January 16, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> as Manny the Butcher<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tKO56PoO1XQ |title=BAD BOYS HAS BEGUN |date=March 21, 2019 |website=YouTube |language=en|access-date=March 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325204331/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tKO56PoO1XQ|archive-date=March 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n\n===Development===\n[[Michael Bay]], the director of the first two ''Bad Boys'' films, stated in June 2008 that he might direct ''Bad Boys 3'', but that the greatest obstacle would be cost considering both Will Smith and himself demanded some of the highest salaries in the film industry.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a97301/smith-wants-to-make-bad-boys-3/ |title=Smith wants to make 'Bad Boys 3' |last=Hilton |first=Beth |date=June 3, 2008 |website=Digital Spy |language=en-GB|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323111151/https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a97301/smith-wants-to-make-bad-boys-3/|archive-date=March 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> By August 2009, Columbia Pictures had hired [[Peter Craig]] to write a script for the sequel.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thefilmstage.com/2009/08/31/bad-boys-3-in-development |title='Bad Boys 3\u2032 In Development |publisher=Thefilmstage.com |date=August 31, 2009 |accessdate=October 2, 2018 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724024723/http://thefilmstage.com/2009/08/31/bad-boys-3-in-development/ |archivedate=July 24, 2011 }}</ref> In February 2011, [[Martin Lawrence]] stated that the film was in development.<ref>[http://www.bet.com/video/themoniqueshow/season2/martin-lawrence-232336.html] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110405050834/http://www.bet.com/video/themoniqueshow/season2/martin-lawrence-232336.html|date=April 5, 2011}}</ref>\n\nFollowing several delays, Jerry Bruckheimer announced in June 2014 that screenwriter [[David Guggenheim]] was working on the storyline for the sequel.<ref>{{cite web |last=Reynolds |first=Simon |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/news/a578677/jerry-bruckheimer-trying-to-get-michael-bay-back-for-bad-boys-3.html?rss |title=Jerry Bruckheimer trying to get Michael Bay back for Bad Boys 3 |website=Digital Spy |date=June 18, 2014 |accessdate=October 2, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924123325/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/news/a578677/jerry-bruckheimer-trying-to-get-michael-bay-back-for-bad-boys-3.html?rss |archive-date=September 24, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref> Two months later, Lawrence said a script had been written and roles had been cast.<ref>{{cite web |author=Martin Lawrence |url=http://teamcoco.com/video/martin-lawrence-bad-boys-3 |title=Martin Lawrence Announces \"Bad Boys 3\" @ |publisher=Teamcoco.com |date=August 14, 2014 |accessdate=October 2, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612164320/http://teamcoco.com/video/martin-lawrence-bad-boys-3 |archive-date=June 12, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> The following year in June 2015, it was reported that director [[Joe Carnahan]] was in early talks to write and possibly direct the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/06/joe-carnahan-bad-boys-3-will-smith-1201440459/ |title=Joe Carnahan Circles 'Bad Boys 3' for Sony |first=Mike Jr. |last=Fleming |website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102084036/https://deadline.com/2015/06/joe-carnahan-bad-boys-3-will-smith-1201440459/|archive-date=January 2, 2019|url-status=live|date=June 10, 2015 }}</ref> [[Sony Pictures Entertainment]] announced a short time later in August 2015 that there were plans for two sequels, with ''Bad Boys 3'' scheduled for release on February 17, 2017, followed by ''Bad Boys 4'' on July 3, 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sony Pictures Dates 16 Films Through 2019! |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/468725-sony-pictures-dates-16-films |accessdate=October 2, 2018 |publisher=ComingSoon.net |date=August 5, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150807171320/http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/468725-sony-pictures-dates-16-films|archive-date=August 7, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> In early 2016, ''Bad Boys 3'' was pushed to June 2, 2017, with no update on the release date of ''Bad Boys 4''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/03/the-dark-tower-presidents-day-weekend-2017-bad-boys-3-men-in-black-21-jump-street-1201714957/ |title=Sony Flush With 2017 Franchises With 'The Dark Tower', 'Bad Boys 3', Barbie & Maybe 'MIB23' Slotted |website=Deadline Hollywood |last=Fleming |first=Mike Jr. |date=March 4, 2016|access-date=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190114123603/https://deadline.com/2016/03/the-dark-tower-presidents-day-weekend-2017-bad-boys-3-men-in-black-21-jump-street-1201714957/|archive-date=January 14, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Producers had planned to begin production in early 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/uncharted-movie-joe-carnahan-video-game-adaptation-bad-boys-3-1201826553/ |title='Bad Boys 3' Director Joe Carnahan to Write 'Uncharted' Adaptation for Sony (EXCLUSIVE) |last=Kroll |first=Justin |last2=Kroll |first2=Justin |date=July 29, 2016 |website=Variety |language=en|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606163809/http://variety.com/2016/film/news/uncharted-movie-joe-carnahan-video-game-adaptation-bad-boys-3-1201826553/|archive-date=June 6, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Another delay surfaced in August 2016, when, to avoid competition with the upcoming [[DC Comics]] film ''[[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|Wonder Woman]]'', the studio pushed the film's release to January 12, 2018.<ref name=\"Retitled BB 4 Life\" /> It was also revealed that the film would be titled ''Bad Boys for Life''.<ref name=\"Retitled BB 4 Life\">{{cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/08/11/bad-boys-3-title-bad-boys-for-life |title=Bad Boys 3 titled Bad Boys For Life, set for January 2018 |last=Robinson |first=Will |date=August 11, 2016 |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |publisher=|access-date=October 2, 2018 |quote=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180715144758/http://ew.com/article/2016/08/11/bad-boys-3-title-bad-boys-for-life/ |archive-date=July 15, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> In an October 2016 interview on ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'', Lawrence said filming might begin in March 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/2016/10/07/martin-lawrence-says-bad-boys-3-may-start-filming-in-march/ |title=Martin Lawrence Says Bad Boys 3 May Start Filming In March |publisher=Comicbook.com |last=Comicbook |first=Joe |date=October 7, 2016 |accessdate=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170513012657/http://comicbook.com/2016/10/07/martin-lawrence-says-bad-boys-3-may-start-filming-in-march|archive-date=May 13, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In December 2016, an updated release date for ''Bad Boys 4'' was set for May 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=D'Alessandro |first1=Anthony |title=\u2018Spider-Man: Homecoming 2\u2019 Shoots Web Around Independence Day 2019; \u2018Bad Boys 4\u2019 Moves To Memorial Day |url=https://deadline.com/2016/12/spider-man-homecoming-2-bad-boys-4-1201867983/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=February 21, 2020 |date=December 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\nSony announced in February 2017 that the film's release would be delayed for a third time to November 9, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/811563-sony-pictures-2018-schedule#/slide/1 |title=Sony Pictures 2018 Schedule Shifts Hotel Transylvania, Bad Boys, Goosebumps and More |date=February 6, 2017 |accessdate=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207192652/http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/811563-sony-pictures-2018-schedule#/slide/1|archive-date=February 7, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The following month, Carnahan left the movie due to scheduling conflicts.<ref>{{cite web |title=Director Joe Carnahan Exits 'Bad Boys 3' (Exclusive) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/director-joe-carnahan-exits-bad-boys-3-984339 |date=March 7, 2017 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119164451/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/director-joe-carnahan-exits-bad-boys-3-984339|archive-date=November 19, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2017, Sony removed the third film from their release schedule, and later in the month Lawrence said the film would not happen.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/08/silver-and-black-marvel-sony-movie-sicario-2-holmes-and-watson-bad-boys-3-release-dates-1202147448/ |title=Sony Dates 'Silver And Black', 'Sicario 2'; Moves 'Holmes And Watson', 'Bad Boys 3' Unset & More |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=August 11, 2017|access-date=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171214160334/http://deadline.com/2017/08/silver-and-black-marvel-sony-movie-sicario-2-holmes-and-watson-bad-boys-3-release-dates-1202147448/|archive-date=December 14, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nPlanning resumed in February 2018 as Belgian directors [[Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah]] were signed in place of Carnahan, and Smith and Lawrence were confirmed to reprise.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://theplaylist.net/bad-boys-life-new-directors-20180131/ |title='Bad Boys For Life' Gets New Directors, Still Dreams Of Being Made |publisher=theplaylist.net |date=February 1, 2018 |access-date=October 2, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813072709/https://theplaylist.net/bad-boys-life-new-directors-20180131/ |archive-date=August 13, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Geek Worldwide reported that the third installment in the ''Bad Boys'' franchise would film from November 2018 to March 2019 in Miami and Atlanta, with the release date scheduled for January 17, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/will-smith-bad-boys-3-bright-2-suicide-squad-2-filming/ |title=Will Smith To Film Bad Boys 3 & Bright 2 Before Suicide Squad 2 |date=August 18, 2018 |website=ScreenRant |language=en-US|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180819113410/https://screenrant.com/will-smith-bad-boys-3-bright-2-suicide-squad-2-filming/|archive-date=August 19, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thegww.com/update-will-smith-sets-production-schedules-for-bad-boys-for-life-and-bright-2-as-suicide-squad-2-is-delayed/|title=UPDATE: Will Smith Sets Production Schedules For 'Bad Boys For Life' and 'Bright 2' As 'Suicide Squad 2' Is Delayed|date=August 18, 2018|website=GWW|language=en-US|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180819051401/https://thegww.com/update-will-smith-sets-production-schedules-for-bad-boys-for-life-and-bright-2-as-suicide-squad-2-is-delayed/|archive-date=August 19, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn October 2018, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' revealed that Sony was close to green-lighting the film's production.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lang |first1=Brent |last2=Kroll |first2=Justin |title='Bad Boys 3' Coming Together as the Revival Plot Thickens at Sony (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/charlies-angels-bad-boys-21-jump-street-1202952231/ |accessdate=October 2, 2018 |work=Variety |date=October 1, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181001211823/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/charlies-angels-bad-boys-21-jump-street-1202952231/ |archive-date=October 1, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> It was reported in December 2018 that [[Joe Pantoliano]] would reprise his role as Captain Howard from the previous films.<ref>{{cite news |last1=N'Duka |first1=Amanda |title=Joe Pantoliano To Return For Sony's 'Bad Boys For Life' Sequel |url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/joe-pantoliano-sony-bad-boys-for-life-sequel-1202514784/ |accessdate=December 6, 2018 |work=Deadline |date=December 5, 2018 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181206115059/https://deadline.com/2018/12/joe-pantoliano-sony-bad-boys-for-life-sequel-1202514784/ |archive-date=December 6, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Kate del Castillo]] joined the cast in early 2019,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/kate-del-castillo-sony-bad-boys-for-life-1202561174/ |title=Kate del Castillo Cast In 'Bad Boys for Life' At Sony |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |first=Amanda |last=N'Duka |date=February 20, 2019 |accessdate=February 20, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190221111949/https://deadline.com/2019/02/kate-del-castillo-sony-bad-boys-for-life-1202561174/|archive-date=February 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and it reported soon after [[Theresa Randle]] would reprise her role as Marcus's wife, Theresa.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.blackfilm.com/read/2019/03/exclusive-theresa-randle-to-reprise-role-in-bad-boys-for-life/ |title=Exclusive: Theresa Randle to Reprise Role in Bad Boys for Life |access-date=April 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190426122509/https://www.blackfilm.com/read/2019/03/exclusive-theresa-randle-to-reprise-role-in-bad-boys-for-life/ |archive-date=April 26, 2019 |url-status=live|date=March 29, 2019 }}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\n[[Principal photography]] began on January 14, 2019, in downtown [[Atlanta]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Production Begins on Bad Boys For Life |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/1025173-bad-boys-for-life-plot-synopsis-revealed |accessdate=January 8, 2019 |date=January 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Bad Boys for Life Begins Production, Will Smith Shares New Photo |url=https://movieweb.com/bad-boys-3-production-start-will-smith-photo/ |accessdate=January 8, 2019 |work=MovieWeb |date=January 7, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107225216/https://movieweb.com/bad-boys-3-production-start-will-smith-photo/ |archive-date=January 7, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Bad Boys III filming shuts down part of Peachtree Rd, slowing down traffic |url=https://www.wsbtv.com/news/local/atlanta/-bad-boys-iii-filming-slows-down-traffic-on-one-of-atlanta-s-busiest-streets/904466757 |work=WSBATL |date=January 14, 2019 |access-date=January 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190115021916/https://www.wsbtv.com/news/local/atlanta/-bad-boys-iii-filming-slows-down-traffic-on-one-of-atlanta-s-busiest-streets/904466757 |archive-date=January 15, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Shooting also took place in [[Mexico City]] in April 2019, as well as in [[Miami]], wrapping on June 7, 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title= Will Smith & Martin Lawrence Celebrate as Bad Boys for Life Wraps |url= https://movieweb.com/bad-boys-3-wraps-production-set-photos/|website=MovieWeb|author=Ryan Scott |accessdate=February 23, 2020 |date=April 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Will Smith Shares Set Video Confirming Bad Boys for Life Wrapped Shooting |url=https://comicbook.com/movies/2019/06/07/will-smith-set-video-bad-boys-for-life-wrapped-shooting/ |last=Aguilar |first=Matthew |publisher=Comic Book |date=June 7, 2019 |accessdate=June 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190619165805/https://comicbook.com/movies/2019/06/07/will-smith-set-video-bad-boys-for-life-wrapped-shooting/|archive-date=June 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Cinematographer]] Robrecht Heyvaert shot the film with [[CineAlta|Sony CineAlta]] VENICE digital cameras and [[Panavision]] Primo, G- and T-Series [[anamorphic format|anamorphic lens]]es.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sonycine.com/articles/-bad-boys-for-life--passes--215m-worldwide-and--120m-domestic---shot-on-venice---official-trailer/|title=\"Bad Boys for Life\" Box Office Cruises Past $215M Worldwide and $120M Domestic - Shot on VENICE - Official Trailer|author=SonyCine Team|work=[[Sony|SonyCine]]|date=January 27, 2020|accessdate=February 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Music===\n{{Main|Bad Boys for Life (soundtrack)}}\nThe film was composed by [[Lorne Balfe]], whose new music was integrated with [[Mark Mancina]]'s themes from the first film. Both trailers for the film include a remix/mashup of \"[[Bad Boys (Inner Circle song)|Bad Boys]]\" by [[Inner Circle (band)|Inner Circle]] (the franchise's theme) and \"[[Bad Boy for Life]]\" by [[P. Diddy]], [[Black Rob]] and Mark Curry.\n\nThe official soundtrack album to the film, ''Bad Boys for Life: The Soundtrack'' was announced by its executive producer, [[DJ Khaled]], and released on the same day as the film. Artists [[Black Eyed Peas]] and [[J Balvin]] recorded a song titled \"[[Ritmo (Bad Boys for Life)|Ritmo]]\", released October 11, 2019, which served as a [[lead single]] for the film's soundtrack.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8532814/black-eyed-peas-j-balvin-ritmo|title=Black Eyed Peas & J Balvin's 'Ritmo' Will Take You Back in Time|last=Fernandez|first=Suzette|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=October 11, 2019|accessdate=October 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011221738/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8532814/black-eyed-peas-j-balvin-ritmo|archive-date=October 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe soundtrack also features tracks by [[Meek Mill]], [[Santana (band)|Santana]], [[City Girls]], [[Quavo]], [[Rick Ross]], [[Rich the Kid]], [[Bryson Tiller]], [[Nicky Jam]], [[Daddy Yankee]], [[Jaden Smith]], [[Farruko]], [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]], [[Lil Jon]], [[Buju Banton]],<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.dancehallmag.com/2020/01/08/music/buju-banton-on-bad-boys-for-life-soundtrack-with-murda-she-wrote.html|title=Buju Banton On 'Bad Boys for Life' Soundtrack With 'Murda She Wrote'|last=Williams|first=Shirvan|magazine=DanceHallMag.com|date=January 8, 2020|accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref> and [[DJ Durel]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/movies/8547565/bad-boys-for-life-movie-soundtrack-track-list|title='Bad Boys For Life' Soundtrack Features Meek Mill, Farruko, City Girls & More: See Full Track List|last=Roiz|first=Jessica|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=January 8, 2020|accessdate=January 8, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108213258/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/movies/8547565/bad-boys-for-life-movie-soundtrack-track-list|archive-date=January 8, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing and release==\nThe first official trailer for ''Bad Boys for Life'' debuted on September 4, 2019,<ref>{{cite web|last=Tingley|first=Anna|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/bad-boys-for-life-trailer-will-smith-martin-lawrence-1203323258/|title='Bad Boys for Life' Trailer: Will Smith and Martin Lawrence Lay Down the Law|website=Variety|date=September 4, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191105151514/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/bad-boys-for-life-trailer-will-smith-martin-lawrence-1203323258/|archive-date=November 5, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and its second trailer was released on November 5.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/bad-boys-3-for-life-trailer-smith-lawrence/|title=Bad Boys for Life Trailer #2: Mike & Marcus Are Back For One Last Ride|author=Sandy Schaefer|work=[[Screen Rant]]|date=November 5, 2019|accessdate=November 5, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191106143751/https://screenrant.com/bad-boys-3-for-life-trailer-smith-lawrence/|archive-date=November 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Its world premiere was held at the [[TCL Chinese Theatre]] on January 14, 2020.<ref name=\"TCL Premiere\"/> Will Smith and Martin Lawrence arrived at the premiere driving a [[Porsche 911#Water-cooled engines (1998\u2013present)|Porsche 911 Carrera 4S]] with the ''Bad Boys'' theme playing loudly from the car's audio system.<ref name=\"TCL Premiere\">{{cite web |last=Jackson |first=Angelique |title=Why Will Smith and Martin Lawrence Reunited for \u2018Bad Boys for Life\u2019 25 Years Later |url=https://variety.com/2020/scene/news/will-smith-martin-lawrence-bad-boys-for-life-25-years-later-jerry-bruckheimer-1203467945/ |accessdate=February 21, 2020 |website=Variety |date=January 15, 2020}}</ref> ''Bad Boys for Life'' was theatrically released in the United States on January 17, 2020, by [[Sony Pictures Releasing]].<ref name=\"Filmoria.co.uk\">{{cite web |url=https://www.filmoria.co.uk/turn-up-the-heat-when-bad-boys-for-life-explodes-onto-4dx-and-screenx-at-cineworld-cinemas/|title=Bad Boys For Life is in UK and Ireland cinemas from 17th January 2020|publisher=Filmoria.co.uk|date= |accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n''Bad Boys for Life'' was released on digital on March 31, 2020 as the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] had resulted in the closure of most theatres in mid March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://movieweb.com/bad-boys-digital-release-date/|title=Bad Boys for Life Gets Early Digital Release This Month|work=[[MovieWeb]]|last=Scott|first=Ryan|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref> The film will be released on 4K Ultra HD, Blu-ray, and DVD on April 21, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/bad-boys-for-life-drives-into-homes-early-1202890664/|title=\u2018Bad Boys For Life\u2019 Driving Into Homes Soon|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n{{As of|2020|3|21|df=US}}, ''Bad Boys for Life'' has grossed $204.4 million in the United States and Canada, and $214.6 million in other territories, for a worldwide total of $419 million, against a production budget of $90 million.<ref name=\"BOM\" /><ref name=\"NUM\" /> It is both the highest-grossing film in the ''Bad Boys'' franchise and the highest-grossing film released in January.<ref name=\"rtbox\">{{cite web|url=https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/article/weekend-box-office-results-bad-boys-for-life-becomes-biggest-january-release-ever-after-17-7-million-weekend/|title=Weekend Box Office Results: ''Bad Boys for Life'' Becomes Biggest January Release Ever After $17.7 Million Weekend|last=Childress|first=Erik|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|date=February 2, 2020|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn the United States and Canada, the film opened opposite ''[[Dolittle (film)|Dolittle]]'', and was initially projected to gross $35\u201345 million from 3,740 theaters during its three-day opening weekend, for a total of around $48 million over the full four-day [[Martin Luther King Jr. Day|MLK weekend]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/can-bad-boys-for-life-succeed-for-sony-where-mib-international-failed/|title=Can 'Bad Boys for Life' Succeed for Sony Where 'MIB: International' Failed?|publisher=[[TheWrap]]|author=Jeremy Fuster|date=January 14, 2020|accessdate=January 15, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115142402/https://www.thewrap.com/can-bad-boys-for-life-succeed-for-sony-where-mib-international-failed/|archive-date=January 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url= https://deadline.com/2020/01/bad-boys-for-life-dolittle-will-smith-robert-downey-jr-1917-oscar-nominations-box-office-1202831808/ |title=Can 'Bad Boys For Life' Keep The Sony Franchise Alive? \u2013 Box Office Preview\n|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author= Anthony D'Alessandro |accessdate=January 15, 2020|date=January 15, 2020}}</ref> After making $23.5 million on its first day (including $6.36 million from Thursday night previews), estimates were raised to $68 million for four days. The film went on to debut to $62.2 million in its first three days, and $73.4 million over four, the second-best opening for the holiday.<ref name=opening>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/bad-boys-for-life-dolittle-1917-weekend-box-office-1202833726/|title=\u2018Bad Boys For Life\u2019 So Great With $100M+ Worldwide; \u2018Dolittle\u2019 Still A Dud With $57M+ Global \u2013 Box Office Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|accessdate=January 19, 2020|date=January 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200120213703/https://deadline.com/2020/01/bad-boys-for-life-dolittle-1917-weekend-box-office-1202833726/|archive-date=January 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It made $34 million in its second weekend and $17.7 million in its third, remaining in first place both times.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://deadline.com/2020/01/bad-boys-for-life-the-gentleman-the-turning-weekend-box-office-1202840184/|title=\u2018Bad Boys For Life\u2019 & \u20181917\u2019 Shooting Past $100M; \u2018The Turning\u2019 Slammed With Second \u2018F\u2019 Of 2020 e|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|accessdate=January 26, 2020|date=January 24, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url= https://deadline.com/2020/01/gretel-hansel-finds-475k-the-rhythm-section-offbeat-with-235k-thursday-night-previews-1202847821/ |title=\u2018Bad Boys For Life\u2019 Scores Over Super Bowl Weekend With $17M+; \u2018Rhythm Section\u2019 Is A Mess\n|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|accessdate=February 2, 2020|date=February 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\n[[IndieWire]] described reviews for ''Bad Boys for Life'' as \"mostly positive.\"<ref name=\"obenson\" /> The review aggregation website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reported an approval rating of 77% based on 249 reviews, and an average rating of 6.22/10.<ref name=\"RT\" /> The website's critics consensus reads, \"Loaded up with action and a double helping of leading-man charisma, ''Bad Boys for Life'' reinvigorates this long-dormant franchise by playing squarely to its strengths.\"<ref name=\"RT\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bad_boys_for_life/|title=Bad Boys for Life (2020)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=February 24, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218160237/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bad_boys_for_life|archive-date=December 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a weighted average score of 59 out of 100, based on 45 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/bad-boys-for-life|title=Bad Boys for Life Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=February 24, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115153628/https://www.metacritic.com/movie/bad-boys-for-life|archive-date=January 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\" on an A+ to F scale, equivalent to the first two films.<ref name=opening/> [[PostTrak]] reported an average rating of 4.5 out of 5 stars, with 73% of respondents saying they would definitely recommend it.<ref name=opening/>\n\n[[Todd McCarthy]] of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' wrote that \"the third time really is the charm,\" and added, \"The two directors roll with ease between raucous comedy and raw drama, to considerable effect, just as they crank up the tension on any number of occasions, occasionally with palpably visceral impact.\"<ref name=\"THRreview\">{{cite web|url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/bad-boys-life-review-1269838 |title='Bad Boys for Life' Film Review|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |author=Tom McCarthy|date=January 15, 2020|accessdate=January 18, 2020}}</ref> David Ehrlich of ''[[IndieWire]]'' gave the film a \"B\" grade, calling it a \"fun, explosive, and even thoughtful action movie,\" and wrote, \"''Bad Boys for Life'' doesn't aim to raise the bar on its genre or rewrite the blockbuster rulebook, but it's a blast watching Lawrence and Smith revisit these characters and find a sensible place for them in the current Hollywood landscape.\"<ref>{{cite news | last=Ehrlich | first=David | url= https://www.indiewire.com/2020/01/bad-boys-for-life-review-will-smith-martin-lawrence-sequel-1202203377/ | title=\u2018Bad Boys for Life\u2019 Review: Will Smith and Martin Lawrence\u2019s Long-Awaited Sequel Delivers the Goods | work=[[IndieWire]] | date=January 15, 2020 | accessdate=January 19, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Sequel==\nFollowing the opening weekend box office success of the film, Sony announced plans for a fourth installment, with Chris Bremner returning to write the script.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/bad-boys-4-works-1269915 |title='Bad Boys 4' in the Works (Exclusive)|website=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=January 17, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"obenson\">{{cite news | last=Obenson | first=Tambay | url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/01/bad-boys-4-sequel-will-smith-martin-lawrence-1202204317/ | title=\u2018Bad Boys\u2019: Fourth Movie Starring Will Smith and Martin Lawrence Is Already Being Planned | work=[[IndieWire]] | date=January 18, 2020 | accessdate=January 19, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://blog.biographypro.xyz/2020/04/bad-boys-for-life-cast-and-review-in.html hindi Review By BiographyPro]\n* [https://www.badboysforlife.movie/ Official website]\n* {{IMDb title|1502397}}\n\n{{wikiquote}}\n\n{{Bad Boys}}\n{{Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah}}\n{{Jerry Bruckheimer}}\n\n[[Category:African-American films]]\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:2020s action comedy films]]\n[[Category:2020s buddy comedy films]]\n[[Category:2020s sequel films]]\n[[Category:Action films featuring female antagonists]]\n[[Category:American action comedy films]]\n[[Category:American buddy comedy films]]\n[[Category:American buddy cop films]]\n[[Category:American films about revenge]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Fictional portrayals of the Miami-Dade Police Department]]\n[[Category:Films about Mexican drug cartels]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Lorne Balfe]]\n[[Category:Films set in 2020]]\n[[Category:Films set in Miami]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Atlanta]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Miami]]\n[[Category:Films set in Mexico City]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Jerry Bruckheimer]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Will Smith]]\n[[Category:Hood films]]\n[[Category:Midlife crisis films]]\n[[Category:Police detective films]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Joe Carnahan]]\n[[Category:Bad Boys (franchise)]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Peter Craig]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Bad Boy for Life}}\n{{short description|2020 film directed by Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah}}\n{{Use American English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Bad Boys for Life\n| image          = Bad Boys for Life poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah|{{unbulleted list|Adil El Arbi|Bilall Fallah}}]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Jerry Bruckheimer]]\n* [[Will Smith]]\n* [[Doug Belgrad]]\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{plainlist|\n* Chris Bremner\n* [[Peter Craig]]\n* [[Joe Carnahan]]\n}}\n| story          = {{plainlist|\n* Peter Craig\n* Joe Carnahan\n}}\n| based on       = {{Based on|Characters|[[George Gallo]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* Will Smith\n* [[Martin Lawrence]]\n* [[Vanessa Hudgens]]\n* [[Alexander Ludwig]] \n* [[Charles Melton (actor)|Charles Melton]]\n* [[Paola N\u00fa\u00f1ez]]\n* [[Kate del Castillo]]\n* [[Nicky Jam]]\n* [[Joe Pantoliano]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Lorne Balfe]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Lorne Balfe to Score 'Bad Boys for Life' |url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2019/07/23/lorne-balfe-to-score-bad-boys-for-life/ |website=Film Music Reporter |accessdate=July 23, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723215204/http://filmmusicreporter.com/2019/07/23/lorne-balfe-to-score-bad-boys-for-life/ |archive-date=July 23, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n| cinematography = Robrecht Heyvaert\n| editing        = {{plainlist |\n* Dan Lebental\n* [[Peter McNulty (film editor)|Peter McNulty]]\n}}\n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Columbia Pictures]]<ref name=\"THRreview\"/>\n* 2.0 Entertainment<ref name=\"THRreview\"/>\n*[[Don Simpson]]/[[Jerry Bruckheimer Films]]<ref name=\"THRreview\"/>\n* [[Overbrook Entertainment]]<ref name=\"THRreview\"/><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/sony-overbrook-entertainment-12-oclock-boys-film-1202463691/ |title=Sony & Overbrook Entertainment Team On Film About Dirt-Bike Riders |access-date=May 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190509124227/https://deadline.com/2018/09/sony-overbrook-entertainment-12-oclock-boys-film-1202463691/ |archive-date=May 9, 2019 |url-status=live |work=deadline.com}}</ref>\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Sony Pictures Releasing]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|01|17}}\n| runtime        = 124 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/bad-boys-life-film-0|title=Bad Boys for Life (15)|website=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|date=January 14, 2020|accessdate=January 15, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115155724/https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/bad-boys-life-film-0|archive-date=January 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| country        = Belgium<br>United States<ref>{{cite web |title= Bad Boys for Life (2020) |url= https://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/5ddbd53927c08 |website= [[British Film Institute]] |access-date= January 18, 2020 }}</ref><ref name=\"NUM\"/>\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $90 million<ref name=BOM/>\n| gross          = $419.1 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{Cite web |url= https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl1182631425/?ref_=bo_da_table_1 |title=Bad Boys for Life (2020) |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]] |accessdate=April 12, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"NUM\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Bad-Boys-For-Life-(Bad-Boys-3)-(2020)#tab=summary|title=Bad Boys for Life (2020)|website=[[The Numbers (website)|The Numbers]]|accessdate=March 17, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230202109/https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Bad-Boys-For-Life-(Bad-Boys-3)-(2020)#tab=summary|archive-date=December 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Bad Boys for Life''''' is a 2020 American [[action comedy]] film directed by [[Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah]] and written by Chris Bremner, [[Peter Craig]] and [[Joe Carnahan]]. The sequel to ''[[Bad Boys II]]'' (2003), it is the third installment in the [[Bad Boys (franchise)|''Bad Boys'' franchise]] and is based on a story by Craig and Carnahan. The film stars [[Will Smith]], [[Martin Lawrence]], [[Vanessa Hudgens]], [[Alexander Ludwig]], [[Charles Melton (actor)|Charles Melton]], [[Paola N\u00fa\u00f1ez]], [[Kate del Castillo]], [[Nicky Jam]], and [[Joe Pantoliano]]. Smith co-produced the film with [[Jerry Bruckheimer]] and [[Doug Belgrad]]. In ''Bad Boys for Life'', [[Miami]] detectives Mike Lowrey and Marcus Burnett investigate a string of murders tied to Lowrey's troubled past.\n\nA third ''Bad Boys'' film was discussed after the success of the second, with [[Michael Bay]] stating he would be interested in returning to direct, but budgetary constraints made going ahead difficult. The film went through several attempts to enter production over the course of a decade, with a variety of writers and directors attached. The project was eventually finalized and green-lit in October 2018, and filming began the following year, lasting from January to June 2019. [[Principal photography]] took place in [[Atlanta]], [[Miami]] and [[Mexico City]].\n\n''Bad Boys for Life'' was theatrically released in the United States on January 17, 2020, by [[Sony Pictures Releasing]], through [[Columbia Pictures]]. The film received mostly positive reviews from critics,<ref name=\"obenson\" /> and has grossed $419 million worldwide, currently making it the [[2020 in film|highest-grossing film of 2020]]. It is also the highest-grossing installment of the series and the biggest January release of all time.\n\n==Plot==\nIsabel Aretas, widow of cartel kingpin Benito, escapes from a Mexican prison with the aid of her son Armando. Isabel sends Armando to Miami, tasking him with recovering a substantial stash of money his father Benito had hidden, as well as assassinating the people responsible for his father's arrest and eventual death in prison. Isabel demands that Armando kill Miami detective Mike Lowrey last.\n\nIn Miami, Mike accompanies his partner Marcus Burnett to the birth of his first grandson. Desiring to spend more time with his family, the aging Marcus tells Mike he intends to retire, to Mike's chagrin. During a party celebrating Marcus' grandson, Mike is shot by Armando and left in a coma for months. Chastised by Isabel for targeting Mike first, Armando continues to assassinate other targets on his list during Mike's convalescence.\n\nFollowing Mike's recovery, he is determined to seek revenge and unsuccessfully attempts to recruit the now-retired Marcus, causing a fall out between them. Mike violently obtains the identity of arms dealer Booker Grassie from an informant. Realizing that Mike will not heed orders to stay away from the investigation, Captain Howard reluctantly allows him to work with the tech-driven team in charge, the Advanced Miami Metro Operations (AMMO), led by Mike's ex-girlfriend Rita. While the team surveils Grassie at an arms deal, Mike determines that the buyers intend to kill Grassie and intervenes, but fails to save him. Later, Marcus is called by Carver Remy, an old informant who believes the assassin is after him. Marcus contacts Mike and the pair travel to Carver, but are too late to save him. Armando escapes after a fistfight with Mike.\n\nCaptain Howard later reveals his intentions to retire as well, offering advice to Mike that he needs to find a path forward in life. He is abruptly assassinated by Armando moments later. The captain's death pulls Marcus out of retirement, but he intends to work as a team with AMMO. They track down Grassie's accountant, who leads them to Lorenzo \"Zway-Lo\" Rodriguez. They infiltrate Zway-Lo's birthday party leading to a destructive car chase. Armando arrives in a helicopter to rescue Zway-Lo but kills him when he blocks Armando's ability to shoot the pursuing Mike. As he lines up a shot, Armando tells Mike \"Hasta el fuego\". Gunfire from Marcus creates cover for Mike, who falls into the river below.\n\nAMMO is shut down because of the failed operation. In private, Mike reveals to Marcus that Armando may be his son. Before partnering with Marcus, Mike worked as an undercover officer in the Aretas cartel where he met Isabel. They fell in love and intended to run away together, using \"Hasta el fuego\" as a secret catchphrase. Mike ultimately remained loyal to the police, realizing how dangerous Isabel had become. Despite Mike's opposition, Marcus and AMMO join him in Mexico City to confront her.\n\nAt the Hidalgo Palace, Mike meets Isabel and scolds her for concealing the truth from him. A shootout quickly ensues between AMMO and Isabel's men. Marcus shoots the pilot of Isabel's support helicopter, causing it to crash into the central lobby and starting a fire. Marcus confronts Isabel, while Mike tries to explain the truth to Armando. Armando begins to beat up Mike, but he refuses to retaliate. Demanding the truth from his mother, Isabel confirms to Armando that Mike is his father. Unable to kill his father, Armando steps back, and Isabel, while aiming for Mike, inadvertently shoots Armando in the chest. Enraged, she attempts to finish Mike, but Rita intervenes and shoots Isabel several times, sending Isabel falling into the flames below. Marcus then begins to fall into the flames, but is saved by both Mike and Armando. Carrying Armando outside, Mike tells his son that things will not be so good for him due to the crimes he committed, but that he would always be there for him.\n\nReturning to Miami, Rita has been promoted to police captain, and the team celebrates her promotion. Mike arranges for Marcus and Theresa to go on a retreat while he takes care of their grandchild. Sometime later, Mike visits a remorseful Armando in prison, and Armando tells Mike that he is atoning for his sins. Mike then enlists his help for a mission, informing him that it would be a chance to pay back some of his debt, and Armando accepts.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Will Smith]] as Detective Lieutenant Michael Eugene \"Mike\" Lowrey\n* [[Martin Lawrence]] as Detective Lieutenant Marcus Miles Burnett\n* [[Vanessa Hudgens]] as Kelly<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/film/bad-boys-life-trailer-reveals-20816984|title=Bad Boys for Life trailer reveals action-packed scenes for Will Smith sequel|last=Knight|first=Lewis|date=2019-11-05|website=mirror|access-date=2019-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191113171551/https://www.mirror.co.uk/film/bad-boys-life-trailer-reveals-20816984|archive-date=November 13, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Alexander Ludwig]] as Dorn\n* [[Charles Melton (actor)|Charles Melton]] as Rafe\n* [[Paola N\u00fa\u00f1ez]] as Rita Secada, head of AMMO, Mike's ex-girlfriend\n* [[Jacob Scipio]] as Armando Aretas\n* [[Kate del Castillo]] as Isabel Aretas\n* [[Nicky Jam]] as Lorenzo \"Zway-Lo\" Rodr\u00edguez<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/bad-boys-sequel-nicky-jam-1203111208/ |title=Reggaeton Star Nicky Jam Joins 'Bad Boys' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |last=Kroll |first=Justin |last2=Kroll |first2=Justin |date=January 18, 2019 |website=Variety |language=en|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190119174400/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/bad-boys-sequel-nicky-jam-1203111208/|archive-date=January 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Joe Pantoliano]] as Captain Conrad Howard\n* [[Theresa Randle]] as Theresa Burnett, Marcus' wife.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/1054885-theresa-randle-will-return-as-marcus-wife-in-bad-boys-for-life |title=Theresa Randle Will Return as Marcus' Wife in Bad Boys for Life |first=Max |last=Evry|website=[[Comingsoon.net]]|date=March 30, 2019|access-date=April 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190405115510/https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/1054885-theresa-randle-will-return-as-marcus-wife-in-bad-boys-for-life |archive-date=April 5, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Massi Furlan]] as Lee Taglin\n* Dennis Greene as Reggie  \n* Bianca Bethune as Megan Burnett, Marcus' daughter\n* [[Michael Bay]] as Wedding MC\n* [[DJ Khaled]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/dj-khaled-bad-boys-sequel-1203108932/ |title=DJ Khaled Joins 'Bad Boys' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |last=Kroll |first=Justin |last2=Kroll |first2=Justin |date=January 15, 2019 |website=Variety |language=en|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190116095949/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/dj-khaled-bad-boys-sequel-1203108932/|archive-date=January 16, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> as Manny the Butcher<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tKO56PoO1XQ |title=BAD BOYS HAS BEGUN |date=March 21, 2019 |website=YouTube |language=en|access-date=March 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325204331/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tKO56PoO1XQ|archive-date=March 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n\n===Development===\n[[Michael Bay]], the director of the first two ''Bad Boys'' films, stated in June 2008 that he might direct ''Bad Boys 3'', but that the greatest obstacle would be cost considering both Will Smith and himself demanded some of the highest salaries in the film industry.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a97301/smith-wants-to-make-bad-boys-3/ |title=Smith wants to make 'Bad Boys 3' |last=Hilton |first=Beth |date=June 3, 2008 |website=Digital Spy |language=en-GB|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323111151/https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a97301/smith-wants-to-make-bad-boys-3/|archive-date=March 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> By August 2009, Columbia Pictures had hired [[Peter Craig]] to write a script for the sequel.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thefilmstage.com/2009/08/31/bad-boys-3-in-development |title='Bad Boys 3\u2032 In Development |publisher=Thefilmstage.com |date=August 31, 2009 |accessdate=October 2, 2018 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724024723/http://thefilmstage.com/2009/08/31/bad-boys-3-in-development/ |archivedate=July 24, 2011 }}</ref> In February 2011, [[Martin Lawrence]] stated that the film was in development.<ref>[http://www.bet.com/video/themoniqueshow/season2/martin-lawrence-232336.html] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110405050834/http://www.bet.com/video/themoniqueshow/season2/martin-lawrence-232336.html|date=April 5, 2011}}</ref>\n\nFollowing several delays, Jerry Bruckheimer announced in June 2014 that screenwriter [[David Guggenheim]] was working on the storyline for the sequel.<ref>{{cite web |last=Reynolds |first=Simon |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/news/a578677/jerry-bruckheimer-trying-to-get-michael-bay-back-for-bad-boys-3.html?rss |title=Jerry Bruckheimer trying to get Michael Bay back for Bad Boys 3 |website=Digital Spy |date=June 18, 2014 |accessdate=October 2, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924123325/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/news/a578677/jerry-bruckheimer-trying-to-get-michael-bay-back-for-bad-boys-3.html?rss |archive-date=September 24, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref> Two months later, Lawrence said a script had been written and roles had been cast.<ref>{{cite web |author=Martin Lawrence |url=http://teamcoco.com/video/martin-lawrence-bad-boys-3 |title=Martin Lawrence Announces \"Bad Boys 3\" @ |publisher=Teamcoco.com |date=August 14, 2014 |accessdate=October 2, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612164320/http://teamcoco.com/video/martin-lawrence-bad-boys-3 |archive-date=June 12, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> The following year in June 2015, it was reported that director [[Joe Carnahan]] was in early talks to write and possibly direct the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/06/joe-carnahan-bad-boys-3-will-smith-1201440459/ |title=Joe Carnahan Circles 'Bad Boys 3' for Sony |first=Mike Jr. |last=Fleming |website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102084036/https://deadline.com/2015/06/joe-carnahan-bad-boys-3-will-smith-1201440459/|archive-date=January 2, 2019|url-status=live|date=June 10, 2015 }}</ref> [[Sony Pictures Entertainment]] announced a short time later in August 2015 that there were plans for two sequels, with ''Bad Boys 3'' scheduled for release on February 17, 2017, followed by ''Bad Boys 4'' on July 3, 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sony Pictures Dates 16 Films Through 2019! |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/468725-sony-pictures-dates-16-films |accessdate=October 2, 2018 |publisher=ComingSoon.net |date=August 5, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150807171320/http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/468725-sony-pictures-dates-16-films|archive-date=August 7, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> In early 2016, ''Bad Boys 3'' was pushed to June 2, 2017, with no update on the release date of ''Bad Boys 4''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/03/the-dark-tower-presidents-day-weekend-2017-bad-boys-3-men-in-black-21-jump-street-1201714957/ |title=Sony Flush With 2017 Franchises With 'The Dark Tower', 'Bad Boys 3', Barbie & Maybe 'MIB23' Slotted |website=Deadline Hollywood |last=Fleming |first=Mike Jr. |date=March 4, 2016|access-date=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190114123603/https://deadline.com/2016/03/the-dark-tower-presidents-day-weekend-2017-bad-boys-3-men-in-black-21-jump-street-1201714957/|archive-date=January 14, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Producers had planned to begin production in early 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/uncharted-movie-joe-carnahan-video-game-adaptation-bad-boys-3-1201826553/ |title='Bad Boys 3' Director Joe Carnahan to Write 'Uncharted' Adaptation for Sony (EXCLUSIVE) |last=Kroll |first=Justin |last2=Kroll |first2=Justin |date=July 29, 2016 |website=Variety |language=en|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606163809/http://variety.com/2016/film/news/uncharted-movie-joe-carnahan-video-game-adaptation-bad-boys-3-1201826553/|archive-date=June 6, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Another delay surfaced in August 2016, when, to avoid competition with the upcoming [[DC Comics]] film ''[[Wonder Woman (2017 film)|Wonder Woman]]'', the studio pushed the film's release to January 12, 2018.<ref name=\"Retitled BB 4 Life\" /> It was also revealed that the film would be titled ''Bad Boys for Life''.<ref name=\"Retitled BB 4 Life\">{{cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/08/11/bad-boys-3-title-bad-boys-for-life |title=Bad Boys 3 titled Bad Boys For Life, set for January 2018 |last=Robinson |first=Will |date=August 11, 2016 |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |publisher=|access-date=October 2, 2018 |quote=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180715144758/http://ew.com/article/2016/08/11/bad-boys-3-title-bad-boys-for-life/ |archive-date=July 15, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> In an October 2016 interview on ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'', Lawrence said filming might begin in March 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/2016/10/07/martin-lawrence-says-bad-boys-3-may-start-filming-in-march/ |title=Martin Lawrence Says Bad Boys 3 May Start Filming In March |publisher=Comicbook.com |last=Comicbook |first=Joe |date=October 7, 2016 |accessdate=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170513012657/http://comicbook.com/2016/10/07/martin-lawrence-says-bad-boys-3-may-start-filming-in-march|archive-date=May 13, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In December 2016, an updated release date for ''Bad Boys 4'' was set for May 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=D'Alessandro |first1=Anthony |title=\u2018Spider-Man: Homecoming 2\u2019 Shoots Web Around Independence Day 2019; \u2018Bad Boys 4\u2019 Moves To Memorial Day |url=https://deadline.com/2016/12/spider-man-homecoming-2-bad-boys-4-1201867983/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=February 21, 2020 |date=December 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\nSony announced in February 2017 that the film's release would be delayed for a third time to November 9, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/811563-sony-pictures-2018-schedule#/slide/1 |title=Sony Pictures 2018 Schedule Shifts Hotel Transylvania, Bad Boys, Goosebumps and More |date=February 6, 2017 |accessdate=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207192652/http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/811563-sony-pictures-2018-schedule#/slide/1|archive-date=February 7, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The following month, Carnahan left the movie due to scheduling conflicts.<ref>{{cite web |title=Director Joe Carnahan Exits 'Bad Boys 3' (Exclusive) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/director-joe-carnahan-exits-bad-boys-3-984339 |date=March 7, 2017 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119164451/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/director-joe-carnahan-exits-bad-boys-3-984339|archive-date=November 19, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2017, Sony removed the third film from their release schedule, and later in the month Lawrence said the film would not happen.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/08/silver-and-black-marvel-sony-movie-sicario-2-holmes-and-watson-bad-boys-3-release-dates-1202147448/ |title=Sony Dates 'Silver And Black', 'Sicario 2'; Moves 'Holmes And Watson', 'Bad Boys 3' Unset & More |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=August 11, 2017|access-date=October 2, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171214160334/http://deadline.com/2017/08/silver-and-black-marvel-sony-movie-sicario-2-holmes-and-watson-bad-boys-3-release-dates-1202147448/|archive-date=December 14, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nPlanning resumed in February 2018 as Belgian directors [[Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah]] were signed in place of Carnahan, and Smith and Lawrence were confirmed to reprise.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://theplaylist.net/bad-boys-life-new-directors-20180131/ |title='Bad Boys For Life' Gets New Directors, Still Dreams Of Being Made |publisher=theplaylist.net |date=February 1, 2018 |access-date=October 2, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813072709/https://theplaylist.net/bad-boys-life-new-directors-20180131/ |archive-date=August 13, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Geek Worldwide reported that the third installment in the ''Bad Boys'' franchise would film from November 2018 to March 2019 in Miami and Atlanta, with the release date scheduled for January 17, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/will-smith-bad-boys-3-bright-2-suicide-squad-2-filming/ |title=Will Smith To Film Bad Boys 3 & Bright 2 Before Suicide Squad 2 |date=August 18, 2018 |website=ScreenRant |language=en-US|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180819113410/https://screenrant.com/will-smith-bad-boys-3-bright-2-suicide-squad-2-filming/|archive-date=August 19, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thegww.com/update-will-smith-sets-production-schedules-for-bad-boys-for-life-and-bright-2-as-suicide-squad-2-is-delayed/|title=UPDATE: Will Smith Sets Production Schedules For 'Bad Boys For Life' and 'Bright 2' As 'Suicide Squad 2' Is Delayed|date=August 18, 2018|website=GWW|language=en-US|access-date=March 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180819051401/https://thegww.com/update-will-smith-sets-production-schedules-for-bad-boys-for-life-and-bright-2-as-suicide-squad-2-is-delayed/|archive-date=August 19, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn October 2018, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' revealed that Sony was close to green-lighting the film's production.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lang |first1=Brent |last2=Kroll |first2=Justin |title='Bad Boys 3' Coming Together as the Revival Plot Thickens at Sony (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/charlies-angels-bad-boys-21-jump-street-1202952231/ |accessdate=October 2, 2018 |work=Variety |date=October 1, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181001211823/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/charlies-angels-bad-boys-21-jump-street-1202952231/ |archive-date=October 1, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> It was reported in December 2018 that [[Joe Pantoliano]] would reprise his role as Captain Howard from the previous films.<ref>{{cite news |last1=N'Duka |first1=Amanda |title=Joe Pantoliano To Return For Sony's 'Bad Boys For Life' Sequel |url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/joe-pantoliano-sony-bad-boys-for-life-sequel-1202514784/ |accessdate=December 6, 2018 |work=Deadline |date=December 5, 2018 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181206115059/https://deadline.com/2018/12/joe-pantoliano-sony-bad-boys-for-life-sequel-1202514784/ |archive-date=December 6, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Kate del Castillo]] joined the cast in early 2019,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/kate-del-castillo-sony-bad-boys-for-life-1202561174/ |title=Kate del Castillo Cast In 'Bad Boys for Life' At Sony |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |first=Amanda |last=N'Duka |date=February 20, 2019 |accessdate=February 20, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190221111949/https://deadline.com/2019/02/kate-del-castillo-sony-bad-boys-for-life-1202561174/|archive-date=February 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and it reported soon after [[Theresa Randle]] would reprise her role as Marcus's wife, Theresa.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.blackfilm.com/read/2019/03/exclusive-theresa-randle-to-reprise-role-in-bad-boys-for-life/ |title=Exclusive: Theresa Randle to Reprise Role in Bad Boys for Life |access-date=April 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190426122509/https://www.blackfilm.com/read/2019/03/exclusive-theresa-randle-to-reprise-role-in-bad-boys-for-life/ |archive-date=April 26, 2019 |url-status=live|date=March 29, 2019 }}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\n[[Principal photography]] began on January 14, 2019, in downtown [[Atlanta]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Production Begins on Bad Boys For Life |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/1025173-bad-boys-for-life-plot-synopsis-revealed |accessdate=January 8, 2019 |date=January 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Bad Boys for Life Begins Production, Will Smith Shares New Photo |url=https://movieweb.com/bad-boys-3-production-start-will-smith-photo/ |accessdate=January 8, 2019 |work=MovieWeb |date=January 7, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107225216/https://movieweb.com/bad-boys-3-production-start-will-smith-photo/ |archive-date=January 7, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Bad Boys III filming shuts down part of Peachtree Rd, slowing down traffic |url=https://www.wsbtv.com/news/local/atlanta/-bad-boys-iii-filming-slows-down-traffic-on-one-of-atlanta-s-busiest-streets/904466757 |work=WSBATL |date=January 14, 2019 |access-date=January 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190115021916/https://www.wsbtv.com/news/local/atlanta/-bad-boys-iii-filming-slows-down-traffic-on-one-of-atlanta-s-busiest-streets/904466757 |archive-date=January 15, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Shooting also took place in [[Mexico City]] in April 2019, as well as in [[Miami]], wrapping on June 7, 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title= Will Smith & Martin Lawrence Celebrate as Bad Boys for Life Wraps |url= https://movieweb.com/bad-boys-3-wraps-production-set-photos/|website=MovieWeb|author=Ryan Scott |accessdate=February 23, 2020 |date=April 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Will Smith Shares Set Video Confirming Bad Boys for Life Wrapped Shooting |url=https://comicbook.com/movies/2019/06/07/will-smith-set-video-bad-boys-for-life-wrapped-shooting/ |last=Aguilar |first=Matthew |publisher=Comic Book |date=June 7, 2019 |accessdate=June 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190619165805/https://comicbook.com/movies/2019/06/07/will-smith-set-video-bad-boys-for-life-wrapped-shooting/|archive-date=June 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Cinematographer]] Robrecht Heyvaert shot the film with [[CineAlta|Sony CineAlta]] VENICE digital cameras and [[Panavision]] Primo, G- and T-Series [[anamorphic format|anamorphic lens]]es.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sonycine.com/articles/-bad-boys-for-life--passes--215m-worldwide-and--120m-domestic---shot-on-venice---official-trailer/|title=\"Bad Boys for Life\" Box Office Cruises Past $215M Worldwide and $120M Domestic - Shot on VENICE - Official Trailer|author=SonyCine Team|work=[[Sony|SonyCine]]|date=January 27, 2020|accessdate=February 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Music===\n{{Main|Bad Boys for Life (soundtrack)}}\nThe film was composed by [[Lorne Balfe]], whose new music was integrated with [[Mark Mancina]]'s themes from the first film. Both trailers for the film include a remix/mashup of \"[[Bad Boys (Inner Circle song)|Bad Boys]]\" by [[Inner Circle (band)|Inner Circle]] (the franchise's theme) and \"[[Bad Boy for Life]]\" by [[P. Diddy]], [[Black Rob]] and Mark Curry.\n\nThe official soundtrack album to the film, ''Bad Boys for Life: The Soundtrack'' was announced by its executive producer, [[DJ Khaled]], and released on the same day as the film. Artists [[Black Eyed Peas]] and [[J Balvin]] recorded a song titled \"[[Ritmo (Bad Boys for Life)|Ritmo]]\", released October 11, 2019, which served as a [[lead single]] for the film's soundtrack.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8532814/black-eyed-peas-j-balvin-ritmo|title=Black Eyed Peas & J Balvin's 'Ritmo' Will Take You Back in Time|last=Fernandez|first=Suzette|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=October 11, 2019|accessdate=October 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011221738/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8532814/black-eyed-peas-j-balvin-ritmo|archive-date=October 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe soundtrack also features tracks by [[Meek Mill]], [[Santana (band)|Santana]], [[City Girls]], [[Quavo]], [[Rick Ross]], [[Rich the Kid]], [[Bryson Tiller]], [[Nicky Jam]], [[Daddy Yankee]], [[Jaden Smith]], [[Farruko]], [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]], [[Lil Jon]], [[Buju Banton]],<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.dancehallmag.com/2020/01/08/music/buju-banton-on-bad-boys-for-life-soundtrack-with-murda-she-wrote.html|title=Buju Banton On 'Bad Boys for Life' Soundtrack With 'Murda She Wrote'|last=Williams|first=Shirvan|magazine=DanceHallMag.com|date=January 8, 2020|accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref> and [[DJ Durel]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/movies/8547565/bad-boys-for-life-movie-soundtrack-track-list|title='Bad Boys For Life' Soundtrack Features Meek Mill, Farruko, City Girls & More: See Full Track List|last=Roiz|first=Jessica|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=January 8, 2020|accessdate=January 8, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108213258/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/movies/8547565/bad-boys-for-life-movie-soundtrack-track-list|archive-date=January 8, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing and release==\nThe first official trailer for ''Bad Boys for Life'' debuted on September 4, 2019,<ref>{{cite web|last=Tingley|first=Anna|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/bad-boys-for-life-trailer-will-smith-martin-lawrence-1203323258/|title='Bad Boys for Life' Trailer: Will Smith and Martin Lawrence Lay Down the Law|website=Variety|date=September 4, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191105151514/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/bad-boys-for-life-trailer-will-smith-martin-lawrence-1203323258/|archive-date=November 5, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and its second trailer was released on November 5.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/bad-boys-3-for-life-trailer-smith-lawrence/|title=Bad Boys for Life Trailer #2: Mike & Marcus Are Back For One Last Ride|author=Sandy Schaefer|work=[[Screen Rant]]|date=November 5, 2019|accessdate=November 5, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191106143751/https://screenrant.com/bad-boys-3-for-life-trailer-smith-lawrence/|archive-date=November 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Its world premiere was held at the [[TCL Chinese Theatre]] on January 14, 2020.<ref name=\"TCL Premiere\"/> Will Smith and Martin Lawrence arrived at the premiere driving a [[Porsche 911#Water-cooled engines (1998\u2013present)|Porsche 911 Carrera 4S]] with the ''Bad Boys'' theme playing loudly from the car's audio system.<ref name=\"TCL Premiere\">{{cite web |last=Jackson |first=Angelique |title=Why Will Smith and Martin Lawrence Reunited for \u2018Bad Boys for Life\u2019 25 Years Later |url=https://variety.com/2020/scene/news/will-smith-martin-lawrence-bad-boys-for-life-25-years-later-jerry-bruckheimer-1203467945/ |accessdate=February 21, 2020 |website=Variety |date=January 15, 2020}}</ref> ''Bad Boys for Life'' was theatrically released in the United States on January 17, 2020, by [[Sony Pictures Releasing]].<ref name=\"Filmoria.co.uk\">{{cite web |url=https://www.filmoria.co.uk/turn-up-the-heat-when-bad-boys-for-life-explodes-onto-4dx-and-screenx-at-cineworld-cinemas/|title=Bad Boys For Life is in UK and Ireland cinemas from 17th January 2020|publisher=Filmoria.co.uk|date= |accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n''Bad Boys for Life'' was released on digital on March 31, 2020 as the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] had resulted in the closure of most theatres in mid March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://movieweb.com/bad-boys-digital-release-date/|title=Bad Boys for Life Gets Early Digital Release This Month|work=[[MovieWeb]]|last=Scott|first=Ryan|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref> The film will be released on 4K Ultra HD, Blu-ray, and DVD on April 21, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/bad-boys-for-life-drives-into-homes-early-1202890664/|title=\u2018Bad Boys For Life\u2019 Driving Into Homes Soon|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n{{As of|2020|3|21|df=US}}, ''Bad Boys for Life'' has grossed $204.4 million in the United States and Canada, and $214.6 million in other territories, for a worldwide total of $419 million, against a production budget of $90 million.<ref name=\"BOM\" /><ref name=\"NUM\" /> It is both the highest-grossing film in the ''Bad Boys'' franchise and the highest-grossing film released in January.<ref name=\"rtbox\">{{cite web|url=https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/article/weekend-box-office-results-bad-boys-for-life-becomes-biggest-january-release-ever-after-17-7-million-weekend/|title=Weekend Box Office Results: ''Bad Boys for Life'' Becomes Biggest January Release Ever After $17.7 Million Weekend|last=Childress|first=Erik|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|date=February 2, 2020|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn the United States and Canada, the film opened opposite ''[[Dolittle (film)|Dolittle]]'', and was initially projected to gross $35\u201345 million from 3,740 theaters during its three-day opening weekend, for a total of around $48 million over the full four-day [[Martin Luther King Jr. Day|MLK weekend]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/can-bad-boys-for-life-succeed-for-sony-where-mib-international-failed/|title=Can 'Bad Boys for Life' Succeed for Sony Where 'MIB: International' Failed?|publisher=[[TheWrap]]|author=Jeremy Fuster|date=January 14, 2020|accessdate=January 15, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115142402/https://www.thewrap.com/can-bad-boys-for-life-succeed-for-sony-where-mib-international-failed/|archive-date=January 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url= https://deadline.com/2020/01/bad-boys-for-life-dolittle-will-smith-robert-downey-jr-1917-oscar-nominations-box-office-1202831808/ |title=Can 'Bad Boys For Life' Keep The Sony Franchise Alive? \u2013 Box Office Preview\n|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author= Anthony D'Alessandro |accessdate=January 15, 2020|date=January 15, 2020}}</ref> After making $23.5 million on its first day (including $6.36 million from Thursday night previews), estimates were raised to $68 million for four days. The film went on to debut to $62.2 million in its first three days, and $73.4 million over four, the second-best opening for the holiday.<ref name=opening>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/bad-boys-for-life-dolittle-1917-weekend-box-office-1202833726/|title=\u2018Bad Boys For Life\u2019 So Great With $100M+ Worldwide; \u2018Dolittle\u2019 Still A Dud With $57M+ Global \u2013 Box Office Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|accessdate=January 19, 2020|date=January 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200120213703/https://deadline.com/2020/01/bad-boys-for-life-dolittle-1917-weekend-box-office-1202833726/|archive-date=January 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It made $34 million in its second weekend and $17.7 million in its third, remaining in first place both times.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://deadline.com/2020/01/bad-boys-for-life-the-gentleman-the-turning-weekend-box-office-1202840184/|title=\u2018Bad Boys For Life\u2019 & \u20181917\u2019 Shooting Past $100M; \u2018The Turning\u2019 Slammed With Second \u2018F\u2019 Of 2020 e|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|accessdate=January 26, 2020|date=January 24, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url= https://deadline.com/2020/01/gretel-hansel-finds-475k-the-rhythm-section-offbeat-with-235k-thursday-night-previews-1202847821/ |title=\u2018Bad Boys For Life\u2019 Scores Over Super Bowl Weekend With $17M+; \u2018Rhythm Section\u2019 Is A Mess\n|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Anthony D'Alessandro|accessdate=February 2, 2020|date=February 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\n[[IndieWire]] described reviews for ''Bad Boys for Life'' as \"mostly positive.\"<ref name=\"obenson\" /> The review aggregation website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reported an approval rating of 77% based on 249 reviews, and an average rating of 6.22/10.<ref name=\"RT\" /> The website's critics consensus reads, \"Loaded up with action and a double helping of leading-man charisma, ''Bad Boys for Life'' reinvigorates this long-dormant franchise by playing squarely to its strengths.\"<ref name=\"RT\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bad_boys_for_life/|title=Bad Boys for Life (2020)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=February 24, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218160237/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bad_boys_for_life|archive-date=December 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a weighted average score of 59 out of 100, based on 45 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/bad-boys-for-life|title=Bad Boys for Life Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=February 24, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200115153628/https://www.metacritic.com/movie/bad-boys-for-life|archive-date=January 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\" on an A+ to F scale, equivalent to the first two films.<ref name=opening/> [[PostTrak]] reported an average rating of 4.5 out of 5 stars, with 73% of respondents saying they would definitely recommend it.<ref name=opening/>\n\n[[Todd McCarthy]] of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' wrote that \"the third time really is the charm,\" and added, \"The two directors roll with ease between raucous comedy and raw drama, to considerable effect, just as they crank up the tension on any number of occasions, occasionally with palpably visceral impact.\"<ref name=\"THRreview\">{{cite web|url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/bad-boys-life-review-1269838 |title='Bad Boys for Life' Film Review|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |author=Tom McCarthy|date=January 15, 2020|accessdate=January 18, 2020}}</ref> David Ehrlich of ''[[IndieWire]]'' gave the film a \"B\" grade, calling it a \"fun, explosive, and even thoughtful action movie,\" and wrote, \"''Bad Boys for Life'' doesn't aim to raise the bar on its genre or rewrite the blockbuster rulebook, but it's a blast watching Lawrence and Smith revisit these characters and find a sensible place for them in the current Hollywood landscape.\"<ref>{{cite news | last=Ehrlich | first=David | url= https://www.indiewire.com/2020/01/bad-boys-for-life-review-will-smith-martin-lawrence-sequel-1202203377/ | title=\u2018Bad Boys for Life\u2019 Review: Will Smith and Martin Lawrence\u2019s Long-Awaited Sequel Delivers the Goods | work=[[IndieWire]] | date=January 15, 2020 | accessdate=January 19, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Sequel==\nFollowing the opening weekend box office success of the film, Sony announced plans for a fourth installment, with Chris Bremner returning to write the script.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/bad-boys-4-works-1269915 |title='Bad Boys 4' in the Works (Exclusive)|website=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=January 17, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"obenson\">{{cite news | last=Obenson | first=Tambay | url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/01/bad-boys-4-sequel-will-smith-martin-lawrence-1202204317/ | title=\u2018Bad Boys\u2019: Fourth Movie Starring Will Smith and Martin Lawrence Is Already Being Planned | work=[[IndieWire]] | date=January 18, 2020 | accessdate=January 19, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{[https://blog.biographypro.xyz/2020/04/bad-boys-for-life-cast-and-review-in.html hindi Review By BiographyPro]}}\n* [https://www.badboysforlife.movie/ Official website]\n* {{IMDb title|1502397}}\n\n{{wikiquote}}\n\n{{Bad Boys}}\n{{Adil El Arbi and Bilall Fallah}}\n{{Jerry Bruckheimer}}\n\n[[Category:African-American films]]\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:2020s action comedy films]]\n[[Category:2020s buddy comedy films]]\n[[Category:2020s sequel films]]\n[[Category:Action films featuring female antagonists]]\n[[Category:American action comedy films]]\n[[Category:American buddy comedy films]]\n[[Category:American buddy cop films]]\n[[Category:American films about revenge]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Fictional portrayals of the Miami-Dade Police Department]]\n[[Category:Films about Mexican drug cartels]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Lorne Balfe]]\n[[Category:Films set in 2020]]\n[[Category:Films set in Miami]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Atlanta]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Miami]]\n[[Category:Films set in Mexico City]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Jerry Bruckheimer]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Will Smith]]\n[[Category:Hood films]]\n[[Category:Midlife crisis films]]\n[[Category:Police detective films]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Joe Carnahan]]\n[[Category: